<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>_x0001_</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from London Councils (PHE001</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I note that your Committee is shortly to scrutinise Public Health England and wanted to take this opportunity to make some brief comments on London Councils’  experience of working with them in London.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It is still early days for the new health structures, including Public Health England, and it is clear that they are still in the process of settling all their ways of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> working and clarifying their role and programmes.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">London Councils has, however, welcomed the active engagement of Public Health England (London Region) in establishing with local authorities and other health partners some pan-London governance structures across health and care.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> They are key partners on the London Health Board and in the London Health Chief Officers’ Group, and have provided invaluable expertise and support to early joint work between boroughs, for example on HIV prevention and sexual health commissioning.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Strong personal relationships have been established and provide a sound foundation to build upon.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Public Health England has already demonstrated its commitment to engage positively with and support Directors of Public Health and their teams in local authorities.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> This support has also helpfully been made available to chief executives and other senior directors as they have worked through local transition issues.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Beyond the issue of transition, London local government has welcomed the clear enthusiasm of PHE for seeking to realise the potential of public health integration with councils in order to secure stronger outcomes for local communities. London’s local authorities are determined to use public health integration as a way of making better places to live and work and PHE’s understanding of, and commitment to this agenda has been welcome.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Some of the current challenges that local authorities in London will be looking for Public Health England to play a role in resolving include:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">working with authorities and Health &amp; Wellbeing Boards to identify key expertise and intelligence needs to support priority public health improvements;</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">supporting the development of the public health workforce, combining both public health expertise and expertise in operating in the local government environment to achieve results;</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">providing clear leadership on national policy and legislative changes to support local work to improve public health;</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ensuring that nationally commissioned public health services, commissioned by NHS England on behalf of Public Health England, are developed and managed in a way that fits with locally commissioned activity; and </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">supporting joint working on outstanding issues, like the transfer of 0-5 years public health functions to local authorities that was delayed until April 2015.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Alongside this, we will welcome them continuing to be an active voice in prompting consideration of public health issues and how they can be addressed through both the health agenda and more widely, to help increase independence and opportunity for all members of our communities. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I hope these comments will be helpful to your deliberations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>